<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Well said Brotha! Hope to see you out there (nt)</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Schwag">Schwag</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 10:30 p.m. 6/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Well said Brotha! Hope to see you out there (nt)<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=16" TARGET=_self>My thoughts on PvP</A> (Ragnar[Eqboard.com])
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> Hello All,

<P>&gt; Im message board admin. Ragnar from Eqboard.com stoping by to
<BR>&gt; pay my respects to this fine site, and share my thoughts on Pvp.
<P>&gt; Ok let me first start off with Uo and my experiances. When I
<BR>&gt; first got on Uo back in the good 'ole days of dread lords, There
<BR>&gt; was a sense of danger every time you set foot outside of town,
<BR>&gt; you didnt just have monsters to deal with you had other players
<BR>&gt; who wanted your head. I can remember looking up to some of the
<BR>&gt; pks like gods, there were so powerful and I was a newbie, well I
<BR>&gt; was lucky enough that a few took me under there wing, and really
<BR>&gt; helped me build up. When I was good enough to hold my own in
<BR>&gt; combat I became a Dread lord and started to Pk. Some of the best
<BR>&gt; memories I have are having battles against other players, I
<BR>&gt; wasnt a jerk about pking, I didnt kill newbies, but I had a few
<BR>&gt; mortal enimies that I would duel to the death every time I met
<BR>&gt; up with them. I had so much fun pking in Uo, well OSI came out
<BR>&gt; with a patch to put a penalty on pks; every time they died they
<BR>&gt; would loose stats, I found this to be quite annoying and soon
<BR>&gt; after left Britannia.
<P>&gt; Eq looks to be doing a pretty good job on Pvp, and I cant wait
<BR>&gt; to get in the lands of Norrath and test it out, on Feb 10th I
<BR>&gt; will have that chance =), I know some people think that PvP isnt
<BR>&gt; roleplaying, but what better way is there to strike fear into
<BR>&gt; the hearts of others than to prove your worth in combat?.
<BR>&gt; Another reason I am all for Pvp is what better AI is there than
<BR>&gt; real people?? real people sont get stuck like mosters do, and
<BR>&gt; you can never predict how another player will react, and
<BR>&gt; monsters dont care who you are, real people will remeber you and
<BR>&gt; want there revenge. It adds a lot of depth to the game.
<P>&gt; Just my 2 cents,
<P>&gt; -Rag
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
